column5: Made it out with infamous "SLY" who guided us and many others in their trucks & cars SAFELY onto Lake Simcoe for an ok day of fishing.  I say "ok" because it was double digit hookups the day before I was told.  Fished away from "The Compound" by about 200 yards and managed some rod bending action Whitefish & Lake Trout. Met up with some old friends and made some new ones.  Fished in 83-87 FOW and used Meegs ("mean green") and Williams Whitefish with Blue holographic tape.   Heres one of my buddy Casey and PB laker thru ice    Group shot with Sly   Can't wait for more this week as I feel a flu coming on.  Sly can be reached @705 437 7880.
some nice looking fish! Thanks for sharing. I have used the flu excuse a lot for fishing realted trips. Works really well!
very nice I was out to that spot on saturday and saw lots of fish being caught..
Looks like a fun day too be sure.  -R-
Was out there sat aswell lots of fish to be had!
Is the second person SLY? What is his name, I think I work with him about a year and half ago on some brick work. I think it was Shawn?
